  "prompt": "What are some common remedies to remove a 3mm kidney stone?",
  "response": "Here are some common approaches for managing a 3mm kidney stone:\n\n1. Medical treatments:\n- Pain medication\n- Alpha-blockers to help pass the stone\n- Increased fluid intake\n- Prescription medications\n\n2. Home remedies:\n- Drink plenty of water (2-3 liters daily)\n- Apply heat to reduce pain\n- Take over-the-counter pain relievers\n- Try natural supplements like citrus juices\n\n3. Medical procedures (if stone doesn't pass naturally):\n- Extracorporeal shock wave lithotripsy (ESWL)\n- Ureteroscopy\n- Percutaneous nephrolithotomy\n\n4. Lifestyle recommendations:\n- Reduce salt intake\n- Limit calcium supplements\n- Avoid high-oxalate foods\n- Moderate protein consumption\n\n5. Monitoring:\n- Regular follow-up with urologist\n- Imaging tests to track stone movement\n- Urine and blood tests\n\nMost 3mm stones can pass naturally within a few weeks with proper hydration and medical guidance. However, consulting a healthcare professional for personalized advice is recommended.",
